 Description:
 The Common Very Low Frequency/Low Frequency (VLF/LF) Receiver (CVR) Increment 2 (CVRi2) program will produce a modular open systems approach (MOSA) compliant, advanced, adaptable VLF/LF
 receiver.

 The Family of Advanced Beyond Line-of-Sight Terminals (FAB-T) Force Element Terminal (FET) program was transferred from Space Force (PE 1203001SF / Weapon System Code (WSC) FET000 /
 Appropriation 3022 / Procurement Space Force (PSF)) to Air Force (Program Element (PE 0303131F)) / WSC CVR000 / Appropriation 3010 / Aircraft Procurement (APAF), Transfer Memo signed 12 Nov 2024.

 Activities funded in this program continue to pay for AN/USQ-225 weapons system modernization, integration into multiple legacy systems, other ongoing Nuclear Command Control & Communications (NC3)
 acquisition programs, and future capabilities for the overall AF NC3 Weapon System (WS).

 The Family of Advanced Beyond Line-of-Sight (BLoS) Terminals (FAB-T) Force Element Terminal (FET) program replaces the Ultra High Frequency (UHF) Milstar terminals and provides secure, protected,
 and survivable communications for the strategic warfighter through airborne-based Military Satellite Communication (MILSATCOM) terminals. The FAB-T FET will provide worldwide nuclear and non-nuclear,
 survivable, anti-jam Low Probability of Detect (LPD)/Low Probability of Intercept (LPI) data and voice communications. The FAB-T FET will be interoperable with Advanced Extremely High Frequency (AEHF),
 Enhanced Polar Systems - Recapitalization (EPS-R), and Evolved Strategic SATCOM (ESS) satellite constellations and will be installed on the B-52 aircraft (threshold).

 The FAB-T FET development program was executed as a Middle Tier of Acquisition (MTA) under R-1 Program Element (PE) 1203001SF, Family of Advanced Beyond Line-of-Sight Terminals (FAB-T). On
 January 15, 2026, SAF/AQ approved the FAB-T FET entry in Major Capability Acquisition (MCA) pathway prior to MS-B and closed the MTA program. This allows FAB-T FET to complete development/testing of
 the production representative unit, and to provide additional time for B-52 to identify the integration solution. Upon completion of B-52 entry into MS-B, FAB-T FET will execute a stacked MS-B/C to begin Low-
 Rate Initial Production. This budget line provides funding for the follow-on production portion of the program.

 RDT&E funding for this exhibit is contained in PE 0303131F.

 Justification:
 This program, P-3A Mod - 9830, COMM 2 Crypto and Data, is a new start.



