Justification:
1.1 Naval Criminal Investigative Services (NCIS) Data Modernization & Analytical Tools: FY27 increase ($2.865M) supports refresh of the IT Lifecycle of the Navy Law Enforcement hosting platform systems
used to host Law Enforcement Sensitive (LES) and Criminal Justice Information System (CJIS) services for the Navy and support collaboration and interoperation with other Law Enforcement partners to include
Department of Justice (DOJ), Department of Homeland Security (DHS), Department of State (State), Military Criminal Investigative Organizations (MCIO), and local/state/tribal Law Enforcement entities.

5.3 Network Drives: FY27 decrease ($0.091M) is due to sustainment of the EMPRS program, providing technology refreshment (TR) throughout the years (evolutionary) as opposed to a TR every eight years.

5.4 Storage Devices: FY27 increase ($0.115M) is due to the reduced quantity of storage devices for Network Devices in association with Electronic Military Personnel Records System (EMPRS) required. Funds
provided for life cycle replacement of storage devices.

5.5 Workstations (Selection (SEL) Board): FY27 increase ($0.069M) is due to reduced requirement for additional workstations in association with workstations for the Selection Board with Electronic Military
Personnel Records System (EMPRS).

5.6 Scanners High Speed: FY27 decrease ($0.112M) is provided for High-Speed Scanners in association with EMPRS. Electronic Military Personnel Records System (EMPRS) is an electronic document/image-
based system that serves as the repository for all Department of the Navy official military personnel record images. Funds provide for life cycle replacement of network devices.

5.7 Peripherals: FY27 decrease ($0.015M) is due to lower peripherals required. Peripherals include items such as removable walls within boardrooms that function as display screen for military personnel record
display, keyboards, printers, monitors, mice for workstations in the boardrooms, etc. Peripherals represent auxiliary and infrastructure components that make up and are associated with the EMPRS system.
EMPRS is the major information system which is mutually supported by infrastructure to conduct 160 selection boards on an annual basis.

5.11 Records Mgmt. Software: FY27 increase ($0.008M) provided for procurement of software in support of the Electronic Military Personnel Records System (EMPRS). Electronic Military Personnel Records
System (EMPRS) is an electronic document/image-based system that serves as the repository for all Department of the Navy official military personnel record images. Funds provide for life cycle replacement of
network devices.

5.13 Data Center Consolidation (DCC): FY27 decrease ($1.644M) supports the consolidation and application migration efforts and ensures that systems are modernized to sustain security requirements. Funding
supports the consolidation and application migration efforts and systems modernization. Funds provided sustainment of data center hardware, software, and licenses for established Component Enterprise Data
Centers (CEDCs) and other approved hosting locations.

9.1 Planning and Decision Aid System (PDAS) Equipment Modernization: FY27 increase FY27 ($0.104M) is due to an increase in the scope of the planned data center procurement.

10.1 - 13.1 (NAVWAR) Maritime Operational Battlespace Command & Control (MOB C2) (formerly MOC): FY27 increase ($9.774M) will support the procurement and fielding of Joint Integrated Voice-Video
Enterprise Systems (JIVES), formerly Naval Video Services (NVS), at one MOC facility required to provide Distributed Command, Control & Communications (C3). FY27 funds will support MOC workstation

