 Justification:
 FY 2027 funding will support:

 Mobility Air Forces (MAF): The modification and enhancement of high fidelity MAF aircrew training and support systems to meet combat readiness needs, to include efforts to ensure full employment of
 Distributed Mission Operations (DMO) capabilities.

 Tactical Data Link Communications Capabilities: FY 2027 efforts include MIDS Modernization, which is a continuous technology development/acquisition strategy for robust interoperable communications for
 MIDS JTRS hosted waveforms. The current phase of this capability is a Link 16 enhancement to the MIDS JTRS known as Block Upgrade 3 (BU3). The modernized capability implements the required software
 and firmware updates necessary to meet the Joint Combatant Commander's prioritized requirements for Integrated Fire Control and Joint Tactical Grid information exchange requirements at the Tactical Edge.
 Upgrades to current fielded terminals began in FY23. Increase in funding between FY 2026 and FY 2027 is due to a higher number of planned BU3 retrofits for existing MIDS JTRS terminals across the Air Force
 for FY 2027.


 FY27 efforts for this modification of Advanced Targeting Pods (ATPs) supports the procurement of various kits and kit upgrades as part of ATP- Technical Insertion (TI) for both the LITENING and Sniper
 targeting pods to provide long-range target acquisition and expanded weapon delivery envelopes for greater aircraft survivability to include implementation and fielding of Band Efficient- Common Data Link (BE-



