 Justification:
 FY 2027 budget request increased due to additional funding efforts supporting the Comprehensive Review and GAO Report recommendations to develop and implement V-22 mid-life upgrade efforts that will
 improve current readiness and safety performance outcomes.

 The primary CV-22 Reliability, Readiness & Enhancements modification in FY 2027 is the Proprotor Gear Box (PRGB). V-22 JPO, working with our industry partners at Bell-Boeing, began fielding an improved
 PRGB that implements X-53 Triple-Melt Steel upgrades. Incorporating this cutting-edge steel alloy into PRGB critical assemblies is expected to reduce wear and mitigate risk of premature gear system failures.
 PRGB enhancements vastly improves safety, reliability and operational readiness for the entire V-22 enterprise.

 Other CV-22 Reliability, Readiness & Enhancements include but not limited to: Gearbox Vibration Monitoring Hard Clutch Engagement (HCE) Osprey Drive System Safety and Health Instrumentation (ODSSHI),
 Mobile User Objective System (MUOS) Compatibility, Ethernet Expansion Device (EED), Flight Control System (FCS), Cockpit Technology Refresh (VeCToR), Global Positioning System (GPS), Joint
 Tactical Terminal (JTT), Electrical Load Management System (ELMS), Engine Air Particle Separator (EAPS), Positioning, Navigation, and Timing (PNT), Department of Navy (DoN) Large Aircraft Infrared
 Countermeasures (LAIRCM) Processor Upgrade (DLPU), Constant Frequency Generator (CFG), Limited Life Aircraft Corrections (LLAC) Leading Edge Angle (LEA), and Awareness Network Capabilities/
 Airborne Mission Network (ABMN), including Specialized Automated Mission Suite-Enhanced Situational Awareness (SAMS-ESA).




