 Description:
 The primary CV-22 Reliability, Readiness & Enhancements modification is the Proprotor Gearbox (PRGB) with improved X-53 triple-melt steel alloy to reduce wear in critical gears and bearings. PRGB
 enhancements vastly improve safety, reliability and operational readiness for the entire V-22 enterprise.

 Modifications encompass numerous engineering change proposals (ECP) that have or will be placed on contract to address a variety of CV-22 weapon system requirements. Additionally, these funds implement
 production kits and other equipment resulting from related RDT&E projects in the CV-22 Reliability, Readiness and Enhancements program, including ODSSHI, LEA, FCS, MUOS, EED, SAMS-ESA, and
 enhanced self-deployment capabilities.

 The Reliability, Readiness and Enhancements modification program improves readiness, operational safety, suitability, and effectiveness; corrects deficiencies identified during operational testing and/or field
 operations; improves aircraft reliability/maintainability; enhances the aircraft's self-deployment capability; enables unrestricted access to worldwide airspace; and enhances the effectiveness of defensive aircraft
 survivability systems. Whenever possible, ECPs/kits are installed in blocks to minimize aircraft down time and maximize efficiency.

 Modification Items indicate which modifications are implemented at the Contract Field Team (CFT) or Organizational/Intermediate levels. Installation schedules reflect only CFT installs.

 CV-22 Reliability, Readiness & Enhancements efforts are segmented into Capability, Reliability, and Survivability modifications. Capability modifications include but are not limited to the following: MUOS
 Compatibility, GPS, PNT EED, and SAMS-ESA. Reliability modifications include but are not limited to the following: CFG, EAPS, ODSSHI, LEA, LLAC, SDC, FCS, VeCToR and PRGB. Survivability
 modifications include but are not limited to the following: DLPU, and JTT. Capability, Reliability, and Survivability A-kit and B-kit quantities reflect phasing of individual kits & modifications in the aggregate.

