 Justification:
 In FY 2027, the CRC will continue to align and integrate the Department of the Air Force (DAF) Battle Network efforts to modernize and standardize deployable data flows, provide agnostic communications
 capabilities, and incorporate modern Advanced Battle Management System (ABMS) standards and components. These efforts include, but not limited to, the purchase of radios and M Code timing source to
 support upgrade of tactical data links, the procurement and integration of MILSATCOM and Proliferated Low Earth Orbit Commercial Satellite Communication (PLEO SATCOM) systems, and procurement of
 prime movers.

 The FY 2027 overall funding level is reduced due to the planned procurement profile of the Remote Radio Secure Voice System (RRSVS) modernization effort. The majority of this procurement occurred in FY
 2025 and FY2026. This investment supports the future Joint Force digital infrastructure by eliminating legacy system obsolescence, incorporating Advanced Battle Management System (ABMS) standards and
 components, and meeting other critical operational mandates.




