 Description:
 This budget line funds Strategic Mission Planning and Execution System (SMPES) Program Element (PE). Legacy PEs 0101324F Integrated Strategic Planning & Analysis Network (ISPAN) and 0301112F
 Nuclear Planning & Execution System (NPES) / National Leadership Command Capability (NLCC) Decision Support Service (DSS) have been consolidated into one SMPES PE 0304100F.

 SMPES is an integrated enterprise solution software system providing the U.S. Air Force (USAF) and U.S. strategic nuclear forces' principal nuclear planning and analysis tools; including tools for consequence
 analysis and deliberate, adaptive, and crisis action planning for strategic deterrence. SMPES consolidates the following six independently managed programs into one system: 1) Mission Planning and Analysis
 System (MPAS); 2) Global Adaptive Planning Collaborative Information Environment (GAP-CIE); 3) NLCC DSS - Nuclear Command and Control (NC2) conference module component; 4) NPES Recapitalization
 (NPES Recap); 5) Force Status Readiness (FSR); and 6) Force Survivability Analysis and Management (FSAM).

 SMPES includes automated data processing equipment (ADPE); multiple networks; software, training, and associated deployable and distributed data processing nodes; a test/development environment; and
 subsidiary systems.

 SMPES develops software to facilitate Nuclear Command and Control (NC2) adaptive planning and execution at fixed and mobile sites in real time, and provides communication interfaces with software
 development, data management, software re-engineering, and operations to include requirements validation and training (formerly known as Nuclear Planning and Execution System Recapitalization [NPES
 Recap]).

 SMPES Data Visualizer is a web-based, collaborative, joint operation planning (JOP) application that enables combatant commanders and strategic leaders to rapidly coordinate on course of action development.
 The SMPES Data Visualizer planning environment provides deliberative planning, crisis action planning, decision support tools, and the Global Situational Awareness Tool (GSAT), supporting combatant
 commanders' visual of geospatial, temporal, and relational planning data (formerly GAP-CIE).

 SMPES will use a four-year life-cycle replacement plan for Cyber Investments to procure required Commercial Off-The-Shelf (COTS) hardware (e.g. servers, storage devices, workstations, peripherals and other
 network components) for installation at all fixed/distributed nodes.

 SMPES FY27 amount increase due to rephasing to align with mission requirements.



