 Description:
 PE 0201130F US Northern Command Communications - P-40A
 a. NORAD AND USNORTHCOM INTEROPERABLE COMMUNICATIONS: This includes mission specific communications enhancements to support extension of Public Switched Telephone Network (PSTN),
 Commercial Internet and Cellular-Wireless/First Responder Network 4G LTE to Civil Authorities from the DoW Satellite Teleports either directly to the Civil Authorities' communications systems or through DoW
 communications systems. This program combines the Interoperable Communications and Joint Tactical Radio System (JTRS) compliant radio handsets to enable the Defense Support of Civil Authorities mission.

 b. DEPLOYABLE COMMUNICATIONS CAPABILITIES SYSTEM LIFE CYCLE MANAGEMENT: The USNORTHCOM Deployable Communications Fleet consists of Emergency Response Vehicles (ERV) Mobile
 Command Platforms (MCP), Rapid Response Kits (RRK) and fly-away communications systems, in expeditionary modular and scalable form factors that can be flown on commercial airlines or military aircraft to
 a nationally declared disaster. (NC J6 DCCS combined the previously approved and funded Cellular System Technical Refresh and Emergency Response Communications System into one consolidated effort).

 PE 0207253F Compass Call - P-40A
 Compass Call is the Air Force's wide-area, standoff, Airborne Electromagnetic Attack (AEA) Command and Control Warfare/Information Operations (C2W/IO) weapon system. The employment of this weapon
 system interrupts the adversary's use of the electromagnetic battlespace and is a key active component in the information battlespace and prosecution of current ground and airborne threats. Compass Call's
 sophisticated electromagnetic attack system is capable of surgical denial and/or disruption of adversary Radio Frequency (RF) communications, radar and sensor systems.

 PE 0207407F Electromagnetic Battle Management (EMBM) - P-40A
 The Department of the Air Force (DAF) Electromagnetic Battle Management (EMBM) program is an automated family of systems/applications linked by common architectures, standards and data that will
 expeditiously receive, analyze, display, employ, and securely distribute friendly, neutral, and adversary Electromagnetic Spectrum (EMS) information. DAF EMBM will consist of five component capabilities;
 the ability to attain, maintain, and monitor the spectrum for EMS Situational Awareness (SA), assessment, and mission planning, decision support with command and control, and training interfaces to all levels
 of EMS Operations (EMSO). DAF EMBM will feed into USSTRATCOM's EMBM-Joint (EMBM-J) at the Combatant Command-level enabling synchronization of Joint Non-Kinetic Fires and enabling resilient
 decision advantage in contested EM environments.

 PE 0207439F Electronic Warfare Integrated Reprogramming (EWIR) - P-40A
 DISTRIBUTED MISSION OPERATIONS AND THREAT CHANGE ANALYSIS: Conducted by the 453rd Electronic Warfare Squadron (453 EWS), EWIR provides analytical capabilities and reachback support
 for DoW acquisition, planning and mission execution activities. These capabilities ensure electronic warfare (EW) systems and integrated combat platforms correctly recognize and respond to enemy, friendly


