Justification:
Funding provides the required command specific operational components to complete the Consolidated Space Operations Facility (CSOF) on Schriever, AFB and the Command and Control Facility (C2F) on
Redstone Arsenal (RSA), Huntsville, AL.

The CSOF supports the Orbital Warfare mission of United States Space Command's subordinate operations center, National Space Defense Center (NSDC), the U.S. Space Forces-Space (S4S) Combined Joint
Force Space Component Commander (CJFSCC), and remote site operations for Combined Space Operations Center (CSpOC). The procurement request provides for the MILCON fit-out to enable NSDC to
provide decision quality information to support the Commander, USSPACECOM. The facility will house current and future primary and alternate Space C2 systems. It will provide the environment to enable the
development of future Space C2 systems and be the prototyping and integration location for USSPACECOM operations centers. Additionally, it will also provide isolated environments for modeling and simulation
and as well as a cyber terrain range. The facility will be a critical component of the USSPACECOM C2 Space Warfighting Terrain.

FY27 increase provides critical funding to support the relocation of USSPACECOM from Colorado to Alabama, ensuring a seamless transition to its new headquarters. The funding encompasses C4IT Fit-Out of
USSPACECOM's C2F along with systems integration to establish a state-of-the-art operational environment, as well as advanced information technology services to maintain mission continuity.

The C2F will be a state-of-the-art foundational weapon system that will underpin USSPACECOM's ability to execute its UCP-mandated responsibilities, ensuring mission success. The procurement request will
enable USSPACECOM to fight and win in the contested environment of space. The facility will house current and future primary and alternate Space C2 systems and data from all USSPACECOM's component
commands. It will provide the environment to enable rapid decision making to enable a superior kill chain beyond that of U.S. adversaries. Additionally, it will also provide isolated and HEMP hardened
environments for orbital dynamics, modeling and simulation, and a cyber terrain range.




