 Justification:
 PE 0207410F Air Operations Center Weapon System:

 FY 2027 procurement funding for Air Operations Center Weapon System (AOC WS) Modifications support integration and fielding of improvements/upgrades of existing 3rd Party applications as well as newly
 developed replacement applications, capital equipment replacement (CER) to address commercial end-of-life/end-of-support/direct mission support components including components associated with C2
 applications (3rd Party commercial and government off the shelf (COTS/GOTS)) and network infrastructure. Funding supports continuing to shift the AOC WS toward a cloud-based commercially managed
 infrastructure and platform as a service (IaaS/ PaaS). These AOC WS Modifications are required for the AOC to keep pace with evolving COTS/GOTS components, Department of War directives, changes in
 the underlying IT and network environment, and to remain interoperable, certified, supportable, and compliant through software engineering solutions, integration, testing, fielding, training, and sustainment of
 new capabilities and upgrades to the AOC WS. AOC Modifications will be accomplished through Agile Release Events, periodic maintenance upgrades, emergency fixes, cyber security improvements and other
 integration activities.

 FY 2027 procurement funds will also be used to support the planned acquisition of commercial IT equipment to implement Trusted Thin Client Phase Information Technology (II), which will incorporate additional
 networks into the Operational Support Facility's secure, internal/external multi-network architecture based on operational requirements. FY 2027 procurement funds will be used to evaluate and implement new
 Command and Control Enterprise Comm-IT capabilities.

 FY 2027 funds will also support Capital Equipment Replacement of the existing on-premise equipment in the Operational Support Facility and Combined AOC - Experimental (CAOC-X) site.

 FY 2027 procurement funds will be used to support multiple comm-IT equipment purchases for the CAOC-X experimentation activities is support of the AOC WS and Air Battle Management System (ABMS)
 Battle Lab environment.

 FY 2027 procurement funds may be used on projects to evaluate AOC Enterprise comm-IT capabilities such as:
 a. Zero Trust end-point technology
 b. Connectivity to the Mission Partner Environment for coalition support
 c. Internet-based secure communication using Commercial Solutions for Classified
 d. Support to Joint All Domain Command and Control operations using Multi-Level Security data transfer capabilities
 e. Integration within the Theater Air Planning System of Systems (TAP-SoS) architecture for the DAF BATTLE NETWORK

 FY 2027 procurement increases due to additional equipment required as part of the ongoing AOC modernization effort.

 PE 0303248F, All Domain Common Platform:


