 Description:
 BASE INFORMATION TRANSPORT INFRASTRUCTURE (BITI) procures base-level network infrastructure (e.g., routers, switches, access points, controllers, cables, and other IT-networking equipment /
 infrastructure components) for unclassified and classified Air Force intranet communications. Base Infrastructure Modernization (BIM), under the BITI Program Element (PE), delivers base-level Air Force
 cyberspace network and integrated information infrastructure for DAF installations (active duty, reserve, and Air National Guard (ANG)) and associated Geographically Separated Units (GSU) at approved
 locations. The BIM portion of the BITI PE encompasses base-level information transport systems, both Air Force Network (AFNET) non-secure intranet protocol router (NIPR) / secure intranet protocol router
 (SIPR) wired and wireless network, supporting base mission requirements for digital voice, data, and video systems. This includes commercial device connectivity, Unified Capabilities (UC), and the management
 systems necessary to manage, protect, and maintain DAF battle networks.

 BIM: Designs, procures, and delivers a modernized, commercial best-practice Enterprise Information Technology as a Service (EITaaS) network. This network provides a comprehensive, holistic wired and
 wireless BAN infrastructure, including inside and outside cabling, for the AFNet NIPR and SIPR. This supports the base-level Air and Space Force cyberspace network and integrated information infrastructure
 for DAF installations (Active Duty, Reserve, and ANG) and associated GSUs at approved locations. BIM supports the DAF initiative to utilize an EITaaS model for IT network operations, maintenance, and
 sustainment. BIM provides base network infrastructure to remediate current bandwidth and performance issues (improving user experience) DAF-wide. This supports growing Service IT demands and
 requirements for the AFNet NIPR and SIPR networks. BIM increases data-to-decision speeds, which is foundational to supporting emerging mission communication requirements.

 The FY2027 funding enables the modernization of 187 Active Duty, Space Force, Reserve, and Air National Guard main operating bases and associated GSUs including the procurement and installation of
 equipment upgrading the AFNET NIPR/SIPR wired and wireless base-level IT infrastructure. BIM modernization includes sustainment through communications squadron manpower augmentation, directly
 supporting the DAF's transition to EITaaS.

 In accordance with Section 1815 of the FY 2008 National Defense Authorization Act (P.L. 110-181), this item is necessary for use by the active and reserve components of the armed forces for homeland defense
 missions, domestic emergency responses, and providing military support to civil authorities.

 Funding for this exhibit is contained in PE 0303004F.




