Justification:
PE 0303089F, CYBERSPACE OPERATIONS SYSTEMS

The FY2027 AFNET funding increase is required to modernize and refresh the DAF's Wide Area Network (WAN), securely connecting all 187 DAF Main Operating Bases (MOBs) and all associated
Geographically Separated Units (GSUs) around the globe, through equipment procured for the AFINC and CSCS Weapon Systems (WS). The AFINC WS will procure Next Generation Gateway (NGG)
equipment to modernize 103 DAF locations. The CSCS WS will create a standardized baseline between NIPR and SIPR networks for more efficient network operations management and install equipment at 67
DAF locations while also prioritizing new technologies that will enhance capabilities and reduce lifecycle costs.

DoW mandates the DAF's full implementation and compliance with Zero Trust cybersecurity capabilities by the end of FY2027. The AFINC WS will procure and install remaining Zero Trust Resource Protection
Suites to expand full capability to all 187 DAF Bases, including but not limited to procurement of modernized routers, firewalls, hosting infrastructure and associated equipment. Additionally, the data transport
infrastructure enabling the DAF's classified and unclassified logical networks (CSCS) also requires modernization, to ensure secure connections between devices operating on the networks and enable day-to-
day network operations throughout the DAF.

The AFNET PE provides a singular capability for the DAF that cannot be logically separated without degrading the DAF network for all users. Funding fluctuations are a result of end-of-life equipment
replacements, and current modernization efforts to continue providing network defense capabilities. Each of the 187 DAF MOBs has a unique equipment requirement based on its complexity. Overall equipment
quantities for AFNET end-items will shift over the FYDP as equipment is replaced or modernized.

AFINC includes, but is not limited to, Gateway e-mail security/DNS upgrades, Dual Path Resiliency, Enclave NIPR Firewall and ASIM Sustainment (ENFASS) (previously under Air Force Cyberspace Defense
(ACD)), base boundaries, SDP Router tech refresh, Information Management System Expansions, and Next Generation Gateway.

CSCS includes, but is not limited to, Vulnerability Management, Area Processing Center and Regional Data Center Consolidations, Installation Service Nodes (ISNs), Comply-to-Connect, and Host Based
Security System (HBSS).




