 Description:
 PE 0201122F US Central Command (USCENTCOM) COMMUNICATIONS

 USCENTCOM directs and enables military operations and activities with allies and partners to increase regional security and stability in support of enduring U.S interests and countering violent extremist
 organizations, competing strategically. The Middle East is an area facing ongoing challenges from regional instability and violent extremists, making USCENTCOM's mission essential to mitigating Direct War
 Enduring Costs (DWEC).

 Procurement funding for PE 0201122F focuses on upgrading USCENTCOM's Command and Control (C2) Systems to maintain this critical information advantage. This includes replacing end-of-life C2 systems
 (thin clients, servers, etc.), Joint Information Environment (JIE) infrastructure, and classified and unclassified voice, data, and video dissemination systems. A key component of this upgrade involves modernizing
 Storage Area Network (SAN) infrastructure and bolstering mission partner networks. This includes, but is not limited to, the CENTCOM Partner Network (CPN), CENTCOM Partner Network Episodic (CPN-X),
 and Mission Partner Environment Information System (MPE-IS). These secure networks facilitate bilateral and multilateral information sharing up to the SECRET RELEASABLE level with coalition partners.
 USCENTCOM J6 requires sustained investment to deliver secure, resilient, and innovative IT services that enable operational advantage, strengthen coalition partnerships, and pre-serve freedom of action in the
 information domain.

 To further enhance C4 capabilities, procurement funding will also transition USCENTCOM's communication architecture to the Command's Collaborative Partner Environment (CPE). The CPE provides seamless
 access to data and applications across multiple devices and networks, directly enabling USCENTCOM's C2 capabilities and supports the accelerated decision-making and targeting cycles envisioned by the
 Combined Joint All Domain Command and Control (CJADC2) concepts.

 Funding for this exhibit contained in PE 0201122F.


 PE 0201131F Service Support to USCENTCOM - Communications




