Justification:
PE 0201122F US Central Command (USCENTCOM) Communications

In FY 2027, USCENTCOM will transition from development to full operational capability of the Collaborative Partner Environment (CPE) with mission partners, enabling innovation, collaboration, and data-driven
operations across USCENTCOM's coalition environment. Leveraging MAVEN Rel capabilities, CPE will empower partners with secure, scalable, and real-time access to mission relevant data. CPE also allows
for accelerated operational decision-making while maintaining strict adherence to Zero Trust security and Identity, Credential, and Access Management (ICAM) standards.

Investment in FY 2027 will also support enhanced resiliency in communication efforts, ensuring Information Technology (IT) services and Command and Control (C2) remain uninterrupted in all conditions,
including contested cyber environments, severe weather events, or wartime scenarios. The CPE also aligns USCENTCOM's hybrid multi-cloud environment with DoW enterprise modernization strategies.


PE 0201131F Service Support to USCENTCOM Communication

In FY 2027 procurement funds for Service Support to USCENTCOM focus on modernizing key infrastructure and capabilities across the AOR. The Datalink communications network, crucial for maintaining
air domain awareness across the AOR, requires advancement to comply with mandates from the National Security Agency, National Telecommunications and Information Agency, as well as Federal Aviation
Agency for Crypto Modernization (including frequency remapping). Securing data usage across domains to expedite open-source intelligence, diverse data sources, and invest in UAS mission execution is an
investment integral for mission assurance and warfighter advancement. For consistent communications, portable satellite communications systems integrated into specific mission areas will be paramount.
Regarding Force Protection and Security evolution, security scanner communication devices will continue to offer a blanket of protection to protect lives in harm's way.

Additional touchpoints with FY 2027 procurement funds involve radio and heightened comms, frequency bands dependent upon intended applications (VHF, UHF, etc.), antenna with varieties of improved ranges
and signals, PTT adapters, weather-resistance cases and transportation equipment, as well as encryption modules for secure communications. Lastly, investing in Communications Container Weapons Systems
as mechanisms inside standard intermodal shipping containers will enable covert transportation and deployment for advanced mobility and flexibility.




