 Description:
 United States Space Command (USSPACECOM) procurement is essential to operationalize two critical USSPACECOM facilities, ensuring our nation can deter conflict and secure superiority in the space
 domain. Procurement is required for the crucial fit-out of the Combined Space Operations Facility (CSOF) at Schriever SFB and the USSPACECOM headquarters Command and Control Facility (C2F) at
 Redstone Arsenal, AL.

 The CSOF requires procurement for the necessary mission systems, security infrastructure, and C4I equipment to support the National Space Defense Center's Orbital Warfare mission.

 The USSPACECOM C2F will equip a foundational, state-of-the-art weapon system that will underpin USSPACECOM's warfighting capabilities. C4IT fit for the C2F provides the environment for rapid decision-
 making and ensuring a superior kill chain against our adversaries. This investment is the bedrock upon which USSPACECOM will build the speed, precision, and decision advantage necessary to defend U.S.
 vital interests.




