INSERT INTO public.procurement_line_years (line_id, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, appr_code, ba, line_number, title, quantity, unit_cost, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$PROC_AIRFOR_NA_L0048$$, 2027, $$Air Force$$, $$PROC_AIRFOR$$, $$AIRFOR$$, NULL, $$48$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$ set may not be exact or sum exactly due to rounding.

 Justification:
 PE 0207418F TACTICAL AIRBORNE CONTROL SYSTEM EQUIPMENT (TACS): FY 2027 funding supports the procurement of additional training devices as needed by the field, the fielding of new capabilities,
 to include Digitally Aided Close Air Support (DACAS) that implements Link16 messages utilized for CAS, and will also address emerging and short notice Diminishing Manufacturing and Material Shortage
 (DMSMS) issues.

 PE 0207423F ADVANCED COMMUNICATIONS SYSTEMS: FY27 funding will be dedicated to procuring Second-Generation Anti-Jam UHF Radio for NATO (SATURN) licenses. These SATURN licenses
 enable AF users to upgrade AF radios from the Have Quick II datalink to the SATURN datalink, and provide secure line of sight voice.

 PE 0207422F THEATER DEPLOYABLE COMMUNICATIONS: FY 2027 funding supports increased Air Combat Command (ACC) requirements. Funding will be used as directed by ACC to provide expeditionary
 communications capabilities to the Deployable Combat Wings. This includes, but is not limited to, providing Agile Communications Packages (ACPs) and Fly Away Communications Terminals (FACTs), to include
 Military Satellite Communications (SATCOM), multi point network extension mesh radios, and commercial SATCOM capabilities.

 PE 0207444F TACTICAL AIR CONTROL PARTY-MODERNIZATION (TACP-M): FY 2027 funding is planned to execute efforts to include but not limited to Air Support Operations Center Modernization (ASOC-
 Mod), TACP Command and Control (C2) (including procuring TACP core computers), procurement of equipment related to Maneuver Gateway (MG), Beyond Line of Site (BLOS) Baseband Backhaul (BB/
 BH), Global Network Access, C2 Shelter/Trailer, Electromagnetic Spectrum (EMS), Tactical Laser Communications, TACP Mobile Communication System (MCS) Kits for TACP MCS Block 3 (Communication
 equipment integrated in Armored Multi-Purpose Vehicles) and TACP MCS Block 4 (Communication equipment integrated in Joint Light Tactical Vehicles), MCS Universal (MCS-U) activities, Deployable
 Communications Package (DCP), procurements supporting both Special Warfare Assault Kit (SWAK) and Tactical Assault Kit (TAKBox)(in support of dismounted efforts), and mounted/dismounted radios/
 peripherals/targeting equipment/Global Positioning System (GPS)/etc., to include required Diminishing Manufacturing Sources (DMS)/testing and Naval Surface Warfare Center (NSWC) Crane support for all
 TACP-M programs, both mounted and dismounted.

 Items requested in FY2027 as identified on the P-5 Exhibit are representative but not limited to the items to be procured. Items procured during execution may change based on critical equipment needed to
 support current Air Force mission requirements. Due to the rapidly changing threat environment, the acquisition program manager has the authority to redirect funding as necessary to meet current slated and
 emerging requirements for operational units.

 In accordance with Section 1815 of the FY 2008 National Defense Authorization Act (P.L. 110-181), this item is necessary for use by the active and reserve components of the Armed Forces for homeland
 defense missions, domestic emergency responses, and providing military support to civil authorities.


