 Description:
 The Mobility Equipment program is a critical component of the National Defense Strategy, essential for executing Geographic Combatant Commanders' Operational Plans (OPLANs) worldwide and supports bed-
 down of deployed forces (personnel, aircraft, and support equipment). Funding will procure Expeditionary Airfield Basing prepositioned stocks, enabling rapid response to contingencies and sustained wartime
 operations, vital for projecting airpower, deterrence, and maintaining global presence.

 The FY 2026 spend plan total of $126,200 thousand of discretionary and $41,000 thousand mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $167,200 thousand. Mandatory funds spend plan includes procurement of
 Airfield Lighting with MALSR (3 total) and Air Rapid Response Kits (14 A1s, 14 A3s, 16 A4s, and 16 A5s).

 This equipment is part of the Air Force's prepositioned war reserve materiel (PWRM) and will be managed in accordance with 10 U.S.C. Sec 2229, Strategic Policy on Prepositioning of Materiel and Equipment.

 Expeditionary Airfield Basing is composed of multiple air base capability packages or unit type codes (UTCs) to include feeding, hygiene, water purification, power production, airfield & base lighting, shelters,
 mobile aircraft arresting systems, and environmental support equipment. This program provides personnel and flightline support at forward operating sites (Establish the Base, Operate the Base). The program
 provides funding to procure new and replacement equipment items, and multimedia packages required to support BEAR training facilities at Silver Flag Sites, Regional Training Sites, Technical Schools,
 Technical Certification Centers, Services Combat Center Training, the 635th Materiel Maintenance Group, and Eagle Flag. Costs include inventory reconstitution, spares and consumables, repairs, and
 procurement of new equipment for upgrades or full UTC replacements.

 Air Rapid Response Kits (ARRK): The ARRK packages are turnkey, self-supporting deployable force support packages that can be quickly deployed or pre-positioned in remote, austere locations for use as
 Expeditionary Forward Operating Bases. The contents of the ARRK kits are all hand-transportable and can be positioned, erected, recovered, and stored without the use of any Material Handling Equipment or
 specialty tools. The entire J1 package is a self-supporting, turnkey 100-person bed-down UTC. The J2 package is Self-supporting Command and Control (C2) suite. The J3 - HVAC (Heating, Ventilation, and Air
 Conditioning) Support kit provides the J1 100-Person Beddown kit with HVAC assets while simultaneously providing power redundancy in the event of enemy attack, natural disaster and/or unforeseen asset
 inoperability. The J4 Fuel Support Kit provides extended operability of ARRK kit fuel consuming equipment including generators and shower/shave water heaters. The J5 - Water Purification Package is a self-
 contained, desalination Water purification unit.

 Environmental - HVAC: Heat Pump to provide cooling, heating via reversing valve (heat pump) and supplemental heat via resistance heat strips. Heating, Ventilating, and Air Conditioning (HVAC) provides
 thermal comfort and acceptable indoor air quality.


