INSERT INTO public.procurement_line_years (line_id, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, appr_code, ba, line_number, title, quantity, unit_cost, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$PROC_AIRFOR_NA_L0060$$, 2027, $$Air Force$$, $$PROC_AIRFOR$$, $$AIRFOR$$, NULL, $$60$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$ set may not be exact or sum exactly due to rounding.

 Justification:
 FY 2027 total of $81,066 thousand discretionary will fund procurement of Global Pre-Positioned War Reserve Materiel Fuels Support Equipment to provide the capability to receive, store, and issue petroleum
 products and support combat and mobility aircraft generation requirements in austere locations. The FY 2027 increase includes $39,648 thousand to procure prepositioned Fuels Support Equipment in direct
 support of increasing readiness, and posturing and sustaining a strong denial defense in the Indo-Pacific in alignment with the Agile Combat Employment concept and the National Defense Strategy. Items
 budgeted within this program include (but are not limited to) collapsible fuel tanks, Agile Fueling System -Air and -Ground, fuel pumping assemblies, fuel servicing platforms, ground fuel issuing service stations,
 additive injector equipment, and secondary containment systems (berms). These items enable aircraft weapon systems to refuel in austere ground environments.

 FY 2027 total also includes $3,647 thousand in support of non-WRM Operational Fuels Requirements.

 The FY 2026 spend plan amount includes $34,794 thousand of discretionary, of which $3,546 thousand is for non-WRM Operational Fuels Requirements, and $29,000 thousand mandatory (reconciliation) for a
 total of $63,794 thousand.

 The FY 2025 spend plan amount includes $24,546 thousand of discretionary funding.


 Planned quantities could change due to price increases, inflation, and supply chain fluctuations.

 Fuels Support Equipment assets significantly impact Contested Logistics and provide a cost-effective mix of investments that operationalize the Agile Combat Employment (ACE) concept (AFDN 1-21) in the
 Indo-Pacific. ACE is a proactive and reactive scheme of maneuver that shifts generation of airpower from large, fixed centralized bases to networks of smaller, dispersed bases. Prepositioned capabilities, ashore
 and afloat, place military equipment and supplies at or near the point of planned use to ensure timely support of Expeditionary Air Forces and other specific forces during the initial phases of an operation. These
 assets provide combatant commanders with initial capabilities and materiel until establishment of a mature and sustained Strategic/Theater Distribution Network (CJSCI 4310.01F).

 This program performs a critical role in Combatant Command (CCMD) requirements to support 5 major Operations Plans (OPLANs) and ensures the objectives of the National Defense Strategy can be executed.

 The Fuels Support Equipment program adheres to:
 10 U.S.C. 2229, Strategic Policy on Prepositioning of Materiel and Equipment.




